The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Calcutta, Aug. 31: Tinplate Company has proposed a simultaneous but unlinked rights issue of equity shares and fully convertible debentures (FCDs). It will give three shares for two held at Rs 45 and five FCDs for eight shares held. The FCDs have been priced at Rs 100. The FCD will be converted on April 1, 2011. Every 11 FCDs will be converted into 20 shares of Rs 55 each.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority is likely to come out with guidelines on maiden floats by insurance firms by October this year. We had two meetings with Sebi and a couple of more are required (to decide on the final guidelines), IRDA chairman J. Hari Narayan said.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 31: Toyota Kirloskar Motors has received over 3,000 bookings for the Fortuner. Toyota had set a target to sell 2,000 Fortuners by December this year. Fortuner was launched this month. The company has already instructed them not to take more orders for the next six to seven months.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The government will charge a uniform license fee from telecom operators for all types of services from the current variable structure, to reduce fee evasion.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 31: Indias fiscal deficit stood at over Rs 1.58 lakh crore in the April-July period, 39.5 per cent of the annual budget estimate of over Rs 4 lakh crore.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 31: Jet Airways India will raise $400 million (nearly Rs 1,955 crore) through various fund raising routes. Shareholders will meet on September 24 to consider the proposal.                                                                                                                           
